1
00:00:00,619 --> 00:00:01,879
Hello and welcome.

2
00:00:01,879 --> 00:00:06,440
Today we’ll talk about volume spread analysis,
I’ll show you how to read the market, BEFORE

3
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:11,210
it moves and you’ll learn to anticipate
where the market is going next based on simple

4
00:00:11,210 --> 00:00:13,970
logic and the power of volume and price.

5
00:00:13,970 --> 00:00:24,800
So if you could, like, subscribe to the channel
and stick around for the full video.

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,970
When using VSA, you should be looking for
two things.

7
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:33,520
Whether the price has been validated by the
volume, or whether there is a divergence with

8
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:34,520
the price.

9
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:40,030
If the price is validated then this confirms
a continuation of the price behavior.

10
00:00:40,030 --> 00:00:46,579
By contrast if there is a divergence, then
this is sending a signal of a potential change.

11
00:00:46,579 --> 00:00:49,940
These are the only things we are constantly
searching for in VSA.

12
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,809
Validation or Divergence.

13
00:00:51,809 --> 00:00:55,170
Before we begin, I want to recommend you a
book I’m currently reading.

14
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:59,629
It’s called “A Complete Guide To Volume
Price Analysis” by Anna Coulling.

15
00:00:59,629 --> 00:01:01,969
I highly recommend this book.

16
00:01:01,969 --> 00:01:10,500
Now let’s further discuss Validation and
Divergence.

17
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:16,710
In this example, we have a wide spread up
candle with small wicks on top and bottom,

18
00:01:16,710 --> 00:01:19,330
and the associated volume is well above average.

19
00:01:19,330 --> 00:01:22,250
So, the volume is validating the price action.

20
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:27,030
Let’s assume each candle represents one
trading day, which is also my preferred time

21
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,810
frame for VSA.

22
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:35,280
In this case we have a market which is bullish,
and has risen strongly in the trading session,

23
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:37,610
closing just below the high of the session.

24
00:01:37,610 --> 00:01:42,990
If this is a valid move then we would expect
to see the effort required to push the market

25
00:01:42,990 --> 00:01:45,360
higher, reflected in the volume.

26
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:50,270
Remember, this is also Wyckoff's third law
of effort vs. result.

27
00:01:50,270 --> 00:01:55,550
It takes effort for the market to rise and
also takes effort for the market to fall,

28
00:01:55,550 --> 00:02:01,280
so if there has been a large change in price
in the session, then we expect to see this

29
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:04,640
validated by a well above average volume bar.

30
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,830
Which we have.

31
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:09,800
Therefore, in this case the volume validates
the price.

32
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:12,590
And from this we can assume two things.

33
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:18,379
First, that the price move is confirmed, and
has not been manipulated by the smart money

34
00:02:18,379 --> 00:02:24,480
or market makers, and second, for the time
being, the market is bullish, and until we

35
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:29,880
see a divergence signaled, then we can continue
to maintain any long position that we may

36
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:32,379
have in the market.

37
00:02:32,379 --> 00:02:37,590
Here we have an example of a narrow spread
candle formed on low volume.

38
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:43,389
In this case the price has risen, but only
marginally higher, and the spread of the candle

39
00:02:43,389 --> 00:02:45,360
is therefore very narrow.

40
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:48,859
The wicks to the top and bottom are once again
small.

41
00:02:48,859 --> 00:02:54,879
The associated volume is well below average
and is once again validating the price action.

42
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:58,080
And the reason is again because of effort
and result.

43
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:03,900
In this case the market has only risen in
price by a small amount, and therefore we

44
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:08,540
would expect to see this reflected in the
volume, which should also be low.

45
00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:14,670
After all, if effort and result validate one
another, the effort required to move the market

46
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:20,670
a few points higher (the result), should only
warrant a small amount of effort (the volume).

47
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:31,180
So once again, we have a true picture with
the volume validating the price.

48
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:33,150
Here we have our first divergence.

49
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:39,299
It is clear we have a wide spread up candle,
and if we follow Wyckoff's third rule, then

50
00:03:39,299 --> 00:03:42,700
this result should be matched by an equal
amount of effort.

51
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:46,500
What we have instead is a big result, from
little effort.

52
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,720
This is a divergence.

53
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:53,870
For a wide spread up candle, we would expect
to see a high volume bar, but here we have

54
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:55,629
a low volume bar.

55
00:03:55,629 --> 00:04:00,379
If we were in a long position in the market
and this appeared, we would immediately start

56
00:04:00,379 --> 00:04:02,569
to question what is happening.

57
00:04:02,569 --> 00:04:04,739
Why has this divergence appeared?

58
00:04:04,739 --> 00:04:07,629
Is it an early warning of a possible trap?

59
00:04:07,629 --> 00:04:13,309
This is a pattern which often occurs at the
start of trading sessions in equity markets.

60
00:04:13,309 --> 00:04:17,549
What is happening here is that the smart money
are trying to 'feel out' the sentiment in

61
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:18,590
the market.

62
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:24,139
The market opens, then the price is pushed
higher to test interest in the market from

63
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:25,400
the buyers.

64
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:28,820
Once again this is a signal of a potential
trap.

65
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:34,400
The move higher is NOT a genuine move but
a fake move, designed to suck traders into

66
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:40,870
weak positions, and also take out stops, before
reversing sharply and moving in the opposite

67
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:42,090
direction.

68
00:04:42,090 --> 00:04:44,979
This is why VSA is so powerful.

69
00:04:44,979 --> 00:04:50,350
Volume and price together reveal the truth
behind market intentions.

70
00:04:50,350 --> 00:04:56,030
In this example we can see a narrow spread
candle with high volume which, once again,

71
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:57,979
is another divergence.

72
00:04:57,979 --> 00:05:03,360
As we saw earlier, a small increase in the
price (result), should only require a small

73
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:07,509
increase in volume (effort), but this is not
the case here.

74
00:05:07,509 --> 00:05:13,659
The small price increase has been generated
by a huge amount of volume, so clearly something

75
00:05:13,659 --> 00:05:15,080
is wrong.

76
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:17,680
There is only one conclusion we can draw.

77
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:22,849
The market is starting to look weak, and this
is a typical pattern that starts to develop

78
00:05:22,849 --> 00:05:27,840
at the top of a bullish trend, or the bottom
of a bearish trend.

79
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:34,460
For example in an established bullish trend,
the market opens, starts to rise a little,

80
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:37,960
and the buyers are now starting to take their
profits.

81
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:44,229
As these positions are closed out, more eager
buyers come in, but the price never rises

82
00:05:44,229 --> 00:05:48,720
as the longs continue to liquidate and take
their profits.

83
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,669
And the cycle repeats throughout the session.

84
00:05:51,669 --> 00:05:56,960
What is actually happening is that the market
has reached a price at which further effort

85
00:05:56,960 --> 00:06:02,840
does not result in higher prices, as each
wave of new buyers is met with longs selling

86
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:06,910
out at this level and taking their profits
'off the table'.

87
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:10,130
So there is no sustained move higher in price.

88
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:15,550
In other words, what this combination of price
and volume is revealing is weakness in the

89
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:17,940
market.

90
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:24,419
Now, VSA is only part of the story.

91
00:06:24,419 --> 00:06:29,849
You need to use a variety of other techniques
to confirm the picture and provide additional

92
00:06:29,849 --> 00:06:31,169
validation.

93
00:06:31,169 --> 00:06:36,569
The most important of these are support and
resistance or supply or demand areas.

94
00:06:36,569 --> 00:06:39,400
This is where the market is pausing, before
reversing.

95
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:44,539
Alternatively, it may simply be a pause point
in a longer term trend, which will then be

96
00:06:44,539 --> 00:06:47,129
validated by our volume analysis.

97
00:06:47,129 --> 00:06:55,479
A breakout from one of these regions of consolidation,
coupled with volume, is always a strong signal.

98
00:06:55,479 --> 00:06:57,250
Trends are equally important.

99
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:03,060
Whenever you see a divergence which sets the
alarm bell ringing, the first step is to establish

100
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:05,419
were you are in any trend.

101
00:07:05,419 --> 00:07:10,169
For example, are you at a possible bottom,
where perhaps the market has been selling

102
00:07:10,169 --> 00:07:14,759
off for some time, but is now looking at a
major reversal?

103
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:19,759
Or perhaps you are in the middle of a trend,
and you are experiencing a minor pull back

104
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:22,500
or reversal in the longer term trend.

105
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:27,639
Deciding where you are in the trend, is where
you bring in some of your other analytical

106
00:07:27,639 --> 00:07:31,689
tools which then help to complement VSA.

107
00:07:31,689 --> 00:07:36,479
In judging where you are in the trend, and
potential reversal points, you will always

108
00:07:36,479 --> 00:07:43,360
be looking at support and resistance, candle
patterns, individual candles, or trend lines.

109
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:54,229
All of this will help to identify where you
are in the price action on the chart.

110
00:07:54,229 --> 00:08:00,470
In this example we have a bullish trend developing
in a rising market, and what is obvious is

111
00:08:00,470 --> 00:08:04,789
that rising prices are followed by rising
volume.

112
00:08:04,789 --> 00:08:07,590
This is exactly what we would expect to see.

113
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:13,469
The first candle forms, a narrow spread up
candle with low volume, which is fine.

114
00:08:13,469 --> 00:08:17,229
The volume validates the price, no divergence
here.

115
00:08:17,229 --> 00:08:22,689
The second candle then begins to form, the
spread of this is wider than the first, and

116
00:08:22,689 --> 00:08:28,129
based on Wyckoff's rule, we expect to see
greater volume that on the first bar, which

117
00:08:28,129 --> 00:08:30,060
is indeed the case.

118
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:35,659
So the uptrend is valid, the volume has validated
the price on both candles.

119
00:08:35,659 --> 00:08:41,229
By the time the third candle starts to form,
and closes with a spread which is wider than

120
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:47,040
both the first and the second, we should expect
a high volume bar which reflects Wyckoff's

121
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,920
third law of effort vs result.

122
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:54,870
Once again, the price action on the candle
has been validated by the volume.

123
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:59,300
The three candles themselves are now validating
the price trend.

124
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:05,220
The price over the three bars has moved higher,
developed into a trend, and the volume is

125
00:09:05,220 --> 00:09:14,260
rising and NOW validating the trend itself.

126
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:19,440
In this example, we have what appears to be
a bullish trend, with the first narrow spread

127
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:22,870
candle followed by relatively low volume.

128
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:27,529
This is fine as the volume is validating the
price and is in agreement.

129
00:09:27,529 --> 00:09:32,980
The second candle then forms and we have a
slightly wider spread candle than the first,

130
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,500
but with high volume.

131
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,649
This appears to be a divergence.

132
00:09:36,649 --> 00:09:40,320
With high volume we would expect to see a
wide spread candle.

133
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:46,660
Instead, we only have a candle which is marginally
wider in price spread than the previous candle,

134
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,880
so this is our first sign.

135
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:54,250
The third candle then forms, and closes as
a wide spread candle, but with volume that

136
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:57,540
is lower than on the previous candle.

137
00:09:57,540 --> 00:10:01,660
Given the spread of the bar, it should be
higher, not lower.

138
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:02,839
Another warning signal.

139
00:10:02,839 --> 00:10:08,839
The fourth candle then forms and closes as
a very wide price spread, but the volume is

140
00:10:08,839 --> 00:10:10,430
even lower!

141
00:10:10,430 --> 00:10:12,700
We now have several divergences here.

142
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:17,440
On second candle we have a modest spread in
price, but high volume.

143
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:22,670
The market should have risen much further
given the effort contained in the volume bar.

144
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:25,010
This is signaling potential weakness.

145
00:10:25,010 --> 00:10:29,860
During the third candle the price spread is
wider than the previous candle, but the volume

146
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,040
is lower.

147
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:33,800
The buying pressure is draining away.

148
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:39,620
Also, we have a market that is rising, but
the volume has fallen on this candle.

149
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:45,120
Rising markets should be associated with rising
volume, NOT falling volume.

150
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:50,529
During the fourth candle, we see further confirmation
that the volume and price on this trend are

151
00:10:50,529 --> 00:10:52,540
no longer in agreement.

152
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:58,459
We have a wide spread up candle and even lower
volume than on previous candles in the trend.

153
00:10:58,459 --> 00:11:03,889
So, the falling volume is confirming that
we have a divergence on the trend, as we expect

154
00:11:03,889 --> 00:11:09,589
to see rising volume with a rising trend,
whereas here we have falling volumes on a

155
00:11:09,589 --> 00:11:10,860
rising trend.

156
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:13,850
What are the conclusions?

157
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:16,440
The problems start with candle two.

158
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:22,430
Here we have effort, but not an equivalent
result in terms of the associated price action.

159
00:11:22,430 --> 00:11:25,940
This is therefore the first sign of possible
weakness.

160
00:11:25,940 --> 00:11:28,800
The market is what is known as 'over bought'.

161
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:34,130
The sellers are moving into the market sensing
an opportunity to short the market.

162
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:40,100
This creates a resistance to higher prices,
which is then confirmed on the third and fourth

163
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:43,899
candles, where volume is falling away.

164
00:11:43,899 --> 00:11:49,350
Smart money have seen this weakness, and are
starting to sell, preparing for a move lower,

165
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:55,360
but continue to mark prices higher, to give
the appearance of a market that is still bullish.

166
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,959
It is not.

167
00:11:56,959 --> 00:12:02,079
This may only be a temporary pause, and not
a major change in trend, but nevertheless,

168
00:12:02,079 --> 00:12:05,940
it is a warning of potential weakness in the
market.

169
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:12,000
The high volume is as a result of an increasing
number of buyers closing out their positions,

170
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:17,390
and taking their profits, whilst the remaining
buyers do not have sufficient momentum to

171
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:19,769
take the market higher.

172
00:12:19,769 --> 00:12:24,130
Smart money are also selling at this level
adding to the volumes.

173
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:28,899
This is the reason why volumes fall on the
next two candles, as they continue to mark

174
00:12:28,899 --> 00:12:33,699
the market higher, but are no longer involved
in the move themselves.

175
00:12:33,699 --> 00:12:37,269
They are trapping traders into weak positions.

176
00:12:37,269 --> 00:12:42,630
The initial weakness appeared on candle two,
which was then FURTHER confirmed by candles

177
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:45,529
three and four.

178
00:12:45,529 --> 00:12:49,130
This is often the sequence of events that
unfolds.

179
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:54,050
Initially we see a divergence that appear
using the single candle analysis.

180
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:59,910
We then wait for other candles to appear,
and analyze them against the initial divergence.

181
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:05,560
In this case, the divergence was confirmed,
with prices continuing to rise on falling

182
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:06,560
volumes.

183
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:11,500
And now we have a market which is apparently
weak, and confirmed as such.

184
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:16,279
The next step is to move to the final level
in our analysis, which is to consider the

185
00:13:16,279 --> 00:13:19,960
analysis in the bigger picture of the chart.

186
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:25,560
This will determine whether what we are seeing
is a minor pull back, or the pre-cursor to

187
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:27,490
a change in trend.

188
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:31,860
If this make sense, make sure you watch our
other VSA tutorial.

189
